{
  "texts": [
    "Rigorous validation, attention to bias mitigation, and careful consideration of ethical guidelines are necessary before deploying LLMs for critical public health tasks (15, 19, 41).",
    "Hybrid approaches in sentiment analysis aim to leverage the strengths of different methodologies-such as lexicon-based, traditional machine learning (ML), and deep learning (DL) models-to potentially improve performance or balance accuracy with interpretability (13).",
    "Various combinations exist.",
    "For instance, lexicon-derived sentiment scores can serve as features for ML models, or ML techniques can help refine domain-specific lexicons.",
    "Within DL, architectural hybrids like combining Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks have been explored."
  ]
}